HEADWORD: Impolite
<hw>Im`po*lite"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>impolitus</ets> unpolishied, pref. <ets>im-</ets> not +
<ets>politus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>polire</ets> to polish, refine. See
<er>Polite</er>.]</ety> <def>Not polite; not of polished manners;
wanting in good manners; discourteous; uncivil; rude.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Im`po*lite"ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Im`po*lite"ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impolitic</ent>⟦br⟧
